  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">One Queen Artemisa, as old stories tell,</l>
     <l n="2" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">When depriv'd of her husband she loved so well,</l>
     <l n="3" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">In respect for the love and affection he'd show'd her,</l>
     <l n="4" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">She reduc'd him to dust, and she drank up the Powder.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">But Queen N**********, of a diff'rent complexion,</l>
     <l n="6" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">When call'd on to order the fun'ral direction,</l>
     <l n="7" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Would have eat her dead lord, on a slender pretence,</l>
     <l n="8" met="--+|--+|--+|--+" line_length="12">Not to show her respect, but â€” to save the expence.</l>
    </lg>
